SINGLE-PHASE k=5 polyphase (pk_k5, k_idx==0 only, L=600, Nyquist=100Hz) at DEFAULT channels (64 128 256). Same parent-window count as the k=1 baseline; each window decimated by 5. RF=125 sub-samples × 5ms = 625 raw-ms (kernels=13/3/4, strides=8/4/4). Compares directly to apr26_multiseed_k5_default (multi-phase, same kernels/channels). At k=5 the phases are most aliased on the unfiltered build, so any gap vs the multi-phase result here is the strongest evidence that the phase-repetition was carrying the K-fold metric inflation.